We first compute the two metrics as follows:

1. Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
 • From the income statement, Gross Profit = 291843.79 and Total Revenue = 836813.79  
 • Therefore, Gross Profit Margin = (291843.79 ÷ 836813.79) × 100 ≈ 34.88%

2. Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities)  
 • From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1919526.63  
 • From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities (Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable) = 5596070.00 + 41840.70 = 5637910.70  
 • Therefore, Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = -1919526.63 ÷ 5637910.70 ≈ -0.34

Thus, the solution is as follows:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "34.88%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-0.34"
  }
}
